com.kuka.roboticsAPI.controllerModel.sunrise.execution

Interface ISPRRuntimeManagementHooks


  • public interface ISPRRuntimeManagementHooks
    Management hooks that can be implemented by classes that can execute SPRs.

    These hooks are called independently from other listeners and callbacks and thus unaffected by them.
    Be careful by implementing these hooks. They must not take long time, must not block or use extensive resources.

    This element is an undocumented internal feature. It is not intended to be used by applications as it might change or be removed in future versions.

      • beforePossibleStateChange

        default com.kuka.util.Pair<SPRState,StopConditionType> beforePossibleStateChange(SPRRuntime sprRuntime,
                                                                                 SPRState currentState,
                                                                                 com.kuka.util.Pair<SPRState,StopConditionType> newState)
        Called when an SPR state change is requested.

        Please Note: The function is also called if no state change is executed in the end.

        Parameters:
        sprRuntime - The SPR for which the state change was requested.
        currentState - The current state of the SPR.
        newState - The requested SPR state.
        Returns:
        null if the processing of the new state will be skipped; otherwise returns the same or converted state change and corresponding stop condition should be processed
